porary art. Meanwhile, elucidatory notes to the translation illuminate its most important features.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aHistory of Religion. 4aMedieval Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aSecond Cycle of Legends.  aThe Golden Legend.  aconversion.  ahagiographic romance.  amarriage.  amendicant.  amysticism.  aoctosyllabic verse.  apassion.  apatronage.  apiety.  arealism.  arhetoric.  arural imagery.  atheology.  avernacular.1 aThomas, Alfred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311143096640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781805432715?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781805432715423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781805432715/original  a978-3-11-143096-6  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles